ctions, environmental flows, and mineral-catalyzed steps. Both Strecker and Bucherer-Bergs pathways, HCN polymer hydrolysis, Fischer-Tropsch-type catalysis, cyanosulfidic photochemistry, and hydrothermal reductive amination are featured, alongside concentration mechanisms (eutectic freezing, mineral adsorption) and product protection (clays, brucite). The network provides redundancy and metabolic relevance, illustrating why glycine is the most abundant amino acid across prebiotic settings, meteorites, comets, and laboratory simulations.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "H\u2082O", "iupac_name": "oxidane", "common_name": "water", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2O/h1H2", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "CO\u2082", "iupac_name": "carbon dioxide", "common_name": "carbon dioxide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CO2/c2-1-3", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_003", "formula": "H\u2082", "iupac_name": "dihydrogen", "common_name": "hydrogen", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2/h1H", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": "Hydrothermal"}, {"id": "mol_004", "formula": "HCN", "iupac_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "common_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CN/c1-2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_005", "formula": "NH\u2083", "iupac_name": "azane", "common_name": "ammonia", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H3N/h1H3", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_006", "formula": "CH\u2082O", "iupac_name": "methanal", "common_name": "formaldehyde", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2O/c1-2/h1H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Hydrothermal"}, {"id": "mol_007", "formula": "NH\u2082CH\u2082CN", "iupac_name": "aminoacetonitrile", "common_name": "aminoacetonitrile", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C2H4N2/c3-1-2-4/h1H2,3H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_008", "formula": "NH\u2082OH", "iupac_name": "hydroxylamine", "common_name": "hyd